article.headline: Indiana State 66, Ball State 65
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- David Moss scored 24 points for Indiana State and the Sycamores held off a late rally to beat Ball State 66-65 Saturday night. Ball State led 37-33 at the half, but a basket by Marcus Howard gave Indiana State (3-3) its final points and a 66-58 lead with 3:45 to go. The Cardinals (3-2) got two free throws by Peyton Stovall, a steal and a breakaway dunk by Terrance Chapman and a 3-pointer by Dennis Trammell with just over a minute to go, and neither team scored the rest of the way. Howard added 16 points and Tyson Schnitker had 11 for Indiana State. Moss, a sophomore guard, was 8-of-10 from the free throw line, where the Sycamores won the game. Ball State outscored Indiana State 60-53 from the field, but the Sycamores hit 13-of-22 foul shots to 5-of-9 by the Cardinals. Skip Mills led Ball State with 13 points off the bench, while Cameron Echols and Robert Owens added 10 points apiece.
